This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the measurement and sampling of the Internet. It could also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses potential biases and representativity of top lists. Additionally, it could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with the creation and correlation of top lists. Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CY) and Systems and Control (cs.SD) are also possible sub-categories as they are related to the study of potential biases and stability of top lists.
